result.execSummary:
The defendant Tirso Nmi Rosado was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver THC (<=200g), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tirso Nmi Rosado in court with attorney Kathleen A Lindgren.  Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty. Ct. 1 and 3 dismissed and read-in. 

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 2:
- Total sentence: 3 1/2 years (Initial Confinement: 18 months, Extended Supervision: 2 1/2 years)  Stayed for 3 years Probation
- Court Costs of $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation; alternate 6 days jail - consecutive
- Restitution of $2000.00 Buy Money to be paid to the Metro Drug Unit as a Condition of Probation
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation; alternate 5 days jail - consecutive
- Conditions of  Probation: Maintain absolute sobriety - no alcohol/drugs unless prescribed and in the amount prescribed. Submit to a formal AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.  DNA Sample if not yet provided.
- 9 months jail Condition Time (nonworking hours) commencing 09/19/2014 by 7:00 p.m.. Non-working hours with standard release conditions
